#: ../../migration.rst:175 fbc02ee1485a48fc8b5328d045409b0d
msgid "Custom Zones"
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:176 0dc8adbd66c4403f86197cd9fb0d558d
msgid ""
"Custom zones are rarely used in NethServer 7 and tipically for very "
"specific tasks. They are required to define a network segment with "
"firewall rules different from those of the primary interface or, more "
"commonly, to correctly manage traffic coming from a network other than "
"the one to which the interface is connected. These zones allow for "
"defining specific behavior for that network segment and ensure correct "
"routing in complex environments (e.g., a port forwarding rule with a "
"remote host destination via MPLS or a VPN tunnel)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:180 fb915a7c715b49eb8f1a5a1abf89cd21
msgid ""
"In NethSecurity, zones work differently from NethServer 7, offering for "
"these cases a much simpler management. Typically, in NethSecurity, all "
"previous configurations made with custom zones can be easily managed "
"**without the need to recreate any custom zone**, thanks to the following"
" default behavior."
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:183 c629624f603b42ef869ec769f8056cd9
msgid "**1. Policy inheritance for incoming traffic**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:185 e0357eae416a4295ba6fe0024cfe725a
msgid ""
"All traffic incoming from a NethSecurity interface automatically inherits"
" the same policies as the connected interface, regardless of the "
"originating network. This includes automatic masquerading when traffic is"
" destined for the internet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:187 48dff5602adc4f4d84db2d70c6782300
msgid "Let's look at an example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:189 a52a1e5003e140c3b8d0d985a22a5f4a
msgid ""
"A local interface named \"office\" is operating on the 192.168.1.0/24 "
"network segment and is assigned to the \"lan\" zone. A gateway with IP "
"192.168.1.220 is connected to the same switch as the \"office\" "
"interface, providing access to the remote network 10.10.10.0/24. The "
"remote network 10.10.10.0/24 must use NethSecurity to reach the internet."
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:193 7a50bdc4f8bc40baafc33cb38d4add3d
msgid ""
"In NethSecurity, no additional configuration is needed, all packets sent "
"to the \"office\" interface are correctly routed, even if they originate "
"from a different network segment. Masquerading is also applied to all "
"outbound packets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:195 aa7efce50e414fd7825eb84f340c5dcf
msgid "**2. No need to create new zones for different segments**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:197 5063901bbcca449fbe2fb8d376e5650d
msgid ""
"Just like policies, standard rules can be applied to this traffic without"
" needing to create a new zone. If you want to apply different policies "
"for this segment, you can simply create standard firewall rules. For "
"convenience, you can use a host set with the CIDR network in firewall "
"objects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:199 02117976bcc94bb5b843c0051b5f3f95
msgid "**3. Routing works seamlessly without extra rules**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../migration.rst:201 52475d8c0e504565bae35a572d2dac22
msgid ""
"Routing for this specific network segment functions correctly without any"
" additional rules or zones. In NethServer 7, it was mandatory to create a"
" zone to ensure proper routing for incoming packets, as mentioned in the "
"initial port forwarding's example."
msgstr ""

